channel.title: Original Sounds Challenge - Winners announced!
channel.description:
<big>This challenge has already ended. You may freely be dismissed.</big>
[quote=Aadam, post:63, topic:17279, full:true] Click or tap the up arrow that is above this quote, to see the winner! It is right here, just wait…… :arrow_up: [/quote]
Make your projects **only** using original sounds. Sweeper is allowed, but vocals are not allowed in this challenge. Also, for drums, you have to use original drums category only. The only categories that are allowed are trap, future bass, future house, electronic music, like electro house, drum and bass, and dubstep. **Dubstep** songs get a **10% bonus** in the challenge because they are hard to make, and drum and bass is also hard to make, and that gives **drum and bass a 5% bonus** also. This challenge will be graded on effort, creativity, quality, and sound. Remember to use your best effort, because I can give you a good ranking if I see you put hard work into it. Tracks must be posted before *January 10, 2019*. The winners will be chosen by *January 15, 2020*, but I chose them early. Hope you enjoy! :slightly_smiling_face:
[quote] * The track must follow every rule up above * Any link is allowed, SoundCloud, project files and even uncompressed WAV * Your track must be at least 45 seconds long * **Your track must be posted before January *10th**,* late entrees do not count * No collaborations are allowed. * Remixes are allowed but they have to be Dubstep, Future Bass, or any type electronic music that is **over 135 tempo** * Imported samples are not allowed * The genre electronic can be *anything* under the electronic category, such as techno. * Feel free to edit your track here after you post it, as long as you repost it before the deadline. * Please do not ask why your track did not win [/quote]
Prize: Will help you on **any** WIP track you need help in (Do not judge me because I am still learning how to make good songs), and a mention on my user card.
